				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Whuppin&#039; Jonathon: Recreating the War of 1812 in Miniature" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Napoleonic Wars are in full swing...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The familiar sight of long lines of scarlet-coated British infantry advance on their enemies, ready to shatter them with their disciplined volleys...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But wait.  The opposing soldiers are in line, not an attack column.  Some of them wear grey, not blue, and they speak English, albeit with a strange accent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;French-speaking troops are on the British side, decked in distinctive &amp;quot;habitant&amp;quot; dress.  On the flanks, buckskin-clad frontiersmen face off against painted Natives, both using tomahawks and scalping knives rather than bayonets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These are not the ordered fields of Europe.  This is the wooded wilderness of North America, where artillery pieces are a rarity and cavalry almost non-existent.  Welcome to the Anglo-American war of 1812.  It's Napoleonics, but not as you know it...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A complete ruleset for recreating the War of 1812 on land in miniature, Whuppin' Jonathon allows you to refight the small-scale but desperate battles that saved Canada and established the United States as a respected world power.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Use of d10 dice exclusively.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules for infantry, cavalry, guns, howitzers, and rockets.  Sample battle to illustrate the game - the battle of Frenchtown.  Includes an easy to follow ready reference sheet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
